Q. If there had been any general attack upon the officers, you must have heard it, being in the house? - A. I must;
Thomas Jones
called to me, and gave me the alarm, that some mischief was going forwards; those of the patrole that were along with me came down.

Q. Did you see Grant? - A. Yes;
Daniel M'Carty
struck him with a broom-stick; he then took a cutlass out of a little boy's hand, and struck him.

Mr. Gurney. (To
Mary Summer
). Q. Mrs. Lacon went out for a rush-light? - A. Yes.
